dataplatform.description: Data for the Data Platform stage.

project_factories.description: Data for the project factories stage.

providers.description: Terraform provider files for this stage and dependent stages.

tfvars.description: Terraform variable files for the following stages.

custom_role_id.description: Map of custom role IDs created in the organization.

custom_roles.description: Map of custom roles resources created in the organization.

firewall_policies.description: Map of firewall policy resources created in the organization.

firewall_policy_id.description: Map of firewall policy ids created in the organization.

organization_id.description: Organization id dependent on module resources.

sink_writer_identities.description: Writer identities created for each sink.

contacts.description: List of essential contacts for this resource. Must be in the form EMAIL -> [NOTIFICATION_TYPES]. Valid notification types are ALL, SUSPENSION, SECURITY, TECHNICAL, BILLING, LEGAL, PRODUCT_UPDATES.

custom_roles.description: Map of role name => list of permissions to create in this project.

firewall_policies.description: Hierarchical firewall policy rules created in the organization.

firewall_policy_association.description: The hierarchical firewall policy to associate to this folder. Must be either a key in the `firewall_policies` map or the id of a policy defined somewhere else.

firewall_policy_factory.description: Configuration for the firewall policy factory.

group_iam.description: Authoritative IAM binding for organization groups, in {GROUP_EMAIL => [ROLES]} format. Group emails need to be static. Can be used in combination with the `iam` variable.

iam_additive.description: Non authoritative IAM bindings, in {ROLE => [MEMBERS]} format.

iam_additive_members.description: IAM additive bindings in {MEMBERS => [ROLE]} format. This might break if members are dynamic values.

iam_audit_config.description: Service audit logging configuration. Service as key, map of log permission (eg DATA_READ) and excluded members as value for each service.

iam_audit_config_authoritative.description: IAM Authoritative service audit logging configuration. Service as key, map of log permission (eg DATA_READ) and excluded members as value for each service. Audit config should also be authoritative when using authoritative bindings. Use with caution.

iam_bindings_authoritative.description: IAM authoritative bindings, in {ROLE => [MEMBERS]} format. Roles and members not explicitly listed will be cleared. Bindings should also be authoritative when using authoritative audit config. Use with caution.

logging_exclusions.description: Logging exclusions for this organization in the form {NAME -> FILTER}.

logging_sinks.description: Logging sinks to create for this organization.

policy_boolean.description: Map of boolean org policies and enforcement value, set value to null for policy restore.

policy_list.description: Map of list org policies, status is true for allow, false for deny, null for restore. Values can only be used for allow or deny.

tag_bindings.description: Tag bindings for this organization, in key => tag value id format.

tags.description: Tags by key name. The `iam` attribute behaves like the similarly named one at module level.

firewall_policies.description: Map of firewall policy resources created in this folder.

firewall_policy_id.description: Map of firewall policy ids created in this folder.

id.description: Folder id.

sink_writer_identities.description: Writer identities created for each sink.
